fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes

Interface ITemplateData


  • public interface ITemplateData
    Data set for merging into a template.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • createHash

        <K,V> ITemplateHash<K,V> createHash(String key)
        Creates a template-compatible key-value dictionary and puts it into the template dataset, with an identifying key.

        This is similar to directly putting an instance of Map into the template data set, however for some template systems, use of an instance of ITemplateHash is more efficient, and can transparently convert arbitrary keys into a formats supported by the template system (for example, FreeMarker can only use string keys).

        Type Parameters:
        K - the key type used to manipulate the dictionary.
        V - the value type contained in the dictionary.
        Parameters:
        key - non-null name identifying the dictionary to create and add to the template.
        Returns:
        the new template-compatible key-value dictionary.
        Since:
        1.0

      • createList

        <V> ITemplateList<V> createList(String key,
                                V... values)
        Creates a template-compatible sequence of values and puts it into the template dataset, with an identifying key.

        Note: to avoid compiler warnings, such as unchecked generics array creation for varargs parameter (when invoking this method with only the key, and no values), you can annotate the statement calling this method with @SuppressWarnings("unchecked").

        Type Parameters:
        V - the value type contained in the list.
        Parameters:
        key - non-null name identifying the sequence to create and add to the template.
        values - optional collection of initial values to add to the list.
        Returns:
        the new template-compatible sequence of values.
        Since:
        1.0
